09/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister George Papandreou says Greece would send troops to Iraq only after a UN decision to establish an international peace force there. 
Quoted in <I>Ta Nea</I> on Monday (8 September), he said Athens would contribute soldiers for humanitarian operations and a medical team. 
Papandreou is to begin a two-day visit to neighbouring Cyprus on Tuesday. 
Foreign ministry spokesman Panos Beglitis says Turkish Cypriot opposition parties rejected Papandreou's invitation to meet. 
(MPA, ANA - 08/09/03)
